text: Andrey Aktauov is a Kazakhstani karateka. He is four-time gold medalist in the men's kumite 55 kg event at the Asian Karate Championships. In 2014, he won the gold medal in the men's kumite 55 kg event at the 2014 Asian Games held in Incheon, South Korea. == Career == At the 2019 Asian Karate Championships held in Tashkent, Uzbekistan he won the gold medal in the men's kumite 55 kg event. == References == Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Kazakhstani male karateka Category:Karateka at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Asian Games medalists in karate Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Kazakhstan Category:Medalists at the 2014 Asian Games
